00:57:58.932 --> 00:58:00.390
GLORIA STEINEM:
Well, what's fun is

00:58:00.390 --> 00:58:03.420
to just change
whatever comes at you,

00:58:03.420 --> 00:58:06.050
and to figure out how you
can creatively change it.

00:58:06.050 --> 00:58:08.520
Like, at my age now,
people are always saying,

00:58:08.520 --> 00:58:11.750
who are you passing
the torch to, right?

00:58:11.750 --> 00:58:13.500
So I always say, wait a minute.

00:58:13.500 --> 00:58:16.690
I'm not giving up my
torch, thank you very much.

00:58:16.690 --> 00:58:18.070
I'm keeping my torch.

00:58:18.070 --> 00:58:22.540
And I am using it to
light other torches.

00:58:22.540 --> 00:58:24.430
Because the whole
idea that there's one

00:58:24.430 --> 00:58:26.140
torch is total bullshit.

00:58:26.140 --> 00:58:28.110
No wonder we don't
know where we're going.

00:58:28.110 --> 00:58:31.520
Everybody needs a torch.

00:58:31.520 --> 00:58:34.455
FEMALE SPEAKER: Anyone here
willing to carry a torch?

00:58:34.455 --> 00:58:35.830
GLORIA STEINEM:
But it's fun just

00:58:35.830 --> 00:58:40.210
to transform images like that,
which are hierarchical images.

00:58:40.210 --> 00:58:42.590
There's one person
with the torch?

00:58:42.590 --> 00:58:44.880
No wonder we're in such
deep shit, you know?

00:58:44.880 --> 00:58:47.870
Nobody knows.

00:58:47.870 --> 00:58:50.040
And it's fun to do that.

00:58:50.040 --> 00:58:57.020
And also, it's fun
to value what is--

00:58:57.020 --> 00:59:00.840
Alice Walker has a wonderful
poem that in something like,

00:59:00.840 --> 00:59:02.460
and this shall be
our revolution.

00:59:02.460 --> 00:59:06.950
We shall value what is plentiful
more than what is rare.

00:59:13.050 --> 00:59:15.620
So in a hierarchical kind
of structure like this,

00:59:15.620 --> 00:59:18.780
you're not supposed to
value laughter or joy.

00:59:22.670 --> 00:59:26.740
And the reason why is because
it happens that laughter

00:59:26.740 --> 00:59:29.710
is the only free emotion.

00:59:29.710 --> 00:59:33.320
You can compel fear, we know.

00:59:33.320 --> 00:59:37.620
You can even compel love if
you're isolated and dependent

00:59:37.620 --> 00:59:38.640
for long enough.

00:59:38.640 --> 00:59:41.670
But you can't compel laughter.

00:59:41.670 --> 00:59:45.370
It happens when two things
come together and make a third.

00:59:45.370 --> 00:59:47.520
It happens when
you have an idea.

00:59:47.520 --> 00:59:49.165
It's like an orgasm of the mind.

00:59:52.090 --> 00:59:54.900
And in original
cultures, especially

00:59:54.900 --> 00:59:58.777
at least in Native American
cultures, there is a figure.

00:59:58.777 --> 01:00:00.110
I've forgotten what he's called.

01:00:00.110 --> 01:00:01.720
Maybe somebody here remembers.

01:00:01.720 --> 01:00:04.180
It's a he or a she, naturally.

01:00:04.180 --> 01:00:06.815
And it's not a jester,
but it's a word like it.

01:00:06.815 --> 01:00:07.540
It's trickster.

01:00:07.540 --> 01:00:08.331
It's the trickster.

01:00:13.240 --> 01:00:16.000
it isn't about making a
king laugh, like a jester.

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:17.930
It's about laughter itself.

01:00:17.930 --> 01:00:22.260
And the idea is that laughter
breaks into the unknown,

01:00:22.260 --> 01:00:24.130
from the known to the
unknown, and you can't

01:00:24.130 --> 01:00:26.674
pray unless you can laugh.

01:00:26.674 --> 01:00:28.340
All right, that's a
pretty good measure.

01:00:28.340 --> 01:00:31.420
Don't go any place where
they won't let you laugh.

01:00:31.420 --> 01:00:34.930
You know that you're
being imprisoned.

01:00:34.930 --> 01:00:38.860
And it's why
monotheistic, patriarchal,

01:00:38.860 --> 01:00:41.740
hierarchical religions
don't let you laugh.

01:00:41.740 --> 01:00:45.650
Whereas the ancient
religions let you laugh.

01:00:45.650 --> 01:00:47.250
It was quite OK.

